# EZM API Structure Guidelines

# Directory Structure
- Follow RESTful conventions for API routes
- Use nested routes for related resources
- Keep route handlers focused and single-responsibility
- Group related endpoints logically

# Move Resources
- /api/moves/[moveId]/layouts - Handle move layouts
- /api/moves/[moveId]/stops - Handle move stops
- /api/moves/[moveId]/items - Handle move items

# Layout Resources
- /api/moves/[moveId]/layouts - List/Create layouts
- /api/moves/[moveId]/layouts/[layoutId] - Single layout operations
- /api/moves/[moveId]/layouts/[layoutId]/rooms - Layout rooms
- /api/moves/[moveId]/stops/[stopId]/layouts - Stop layouts

# Stop Resources
- /api/moves/[moveId]/stops - List/Create stops
- /api/moves/[moveId]/stops/[stopId] - Single stop operations
- /api/moves/[moveId]/stops/[stopId]/layouts - Stop layouts
- /api/moves/[moveId]/stops/[stopId]/items - Stop items

# API Implementation
- Use Next.js App Router conventions
- Implement proper error handling
- Use Prisma for database operations
- Validate all inputs
- Return consistent response formats
- Use proper HTTP status codes

# Response Format
```typescript
{
  success: boolean;
  data?: any;
  error?: {
    message: string;
    code?: string;
    details?: any;
  };
}
```

# Error Handling
- 400: Bad Request (validation errors)
- 401: Unauthorized (auth required)
- 403: Forbidden (no access)
- 404: Not Found
- 409: Conflict (unique constraint)
- 500: Internal Server Error

# Authentication
- Check session in every route
- Verify user access to resources
- Handle unauthorized access properly

# Prisma Relations
- Use proper relation syntax
- Include all necessary relations
- Handle unique constraints
- Use transactions when needed

# Schema Compliance
- Match all schema fields
- Handle optional fields
- Respect default values
- Include required relations 